1
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:45,800
Run for Young

2
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:58,320
Those sausages and bacon at Doggo's door

3
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:01,200
were made by us together

4
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,960
with Uncle Tu during the Spring Festival.

5
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:07,600
You miss uncle Tu too?

6
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:12,640
I used to see Uncle Tu and Doggo

7
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,240
making a noise and all that

8
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:17,760
whenever I stood on the balcony.

9
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,600
Now it's so quiet.

10
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,120
Why...

11
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:28,520
Why did it happen so suddenly?

12
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,000
Liang,

13
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,640
everyone has their own fate.

14
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:37,880
You'll understand when you're older.

15
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:42,920
Something's out of our control.

16
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:55,120
What's Doggo gonna do?

17
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:58,720
Will he move in with his mom?

18
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:05,040
I won't be able to see him then...

19
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,480
It's alright,

20
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:08,840
don't worry now.

21
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:09,880
This

22
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,240
depends on himself.

23
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:14,240
Actually,

24
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,880
I've long seen him

25
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:18,000
as my own child.

26
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,720
Whether he leaves

27
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:22,080
or stays,

28
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:24,280
I'll treat him just the same old way.

29
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:28,200
I'll make sure he's fed and kept warm.

30
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,360
Don't worry.

31
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:37,120
It's ok.

32
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:46,880
Episode 10 The Moon Speaks For Me

33
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,760
Who's on duty today? Why is the blackboard not wiped?

34
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:01,040
Tu...

35
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,600
Doggo should be back by now.

36
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:16,520
No idea.

37
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:18,520
He finally made it to the last term,

38
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:19,960
would he just drop out like this?

39
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,200
There's still the College Entrance Exam.

40
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:24,000
Will Doggo be astray then?

41
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,760
What're you talking about! Watch your mouth!

42
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:28,000
It's so strange not having him around.

43
00:04:29,279 --> 00:04:31,120
You live so close,

44
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:33,280
don't you know what he's been up to nowadays?

45
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,200
He leaves the house early and comes back late.

46
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,520
We barely see him.

47
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,160
Stop being paranoid!

48
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,560
Let's go find him together tomorrow!

49
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:42,080
Let's go.

50
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:50,280
Looking at Doggo's empty desk these days,

51
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:53,320
I remembered when the term first started,

52
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:55,120
he told me he wanted to go to college.

53
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:58,120
Who would've thought

54
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,560
something like this would happen.

55
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,560
Yeah...

56
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:07,240
It was such a surprise to see someone

57
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:09,720
so cheeky like him want to work hard for once,

58
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:11,920
but then this happened...

59
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:16,360
Do you think he's not planning on coming back to school?

60
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,600
Looks like it.

61
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:23,480
It was his closest family member he lost.

62
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,040
Must be difficult to accept.

63
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,480
Looking at him like this

64
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:33,320
reminds me how I was like

65
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:34,880
back then.

66
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:38,320
He was the one that was there for me quietly,

67
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,840
waiting for me to come out of that phase.

68
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:42,360
Must have been difficult on him.

69
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:50,400
Who do you think

70
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:51,920
is taking care of him?

71
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:55,080
Will he keep himself warm and fed?

72
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,040
You're worrying too much.

73
00:05:57,640 --> 00:05:58,960
There's Jiao,

74
00:05:59,280 --> 00:05:59,960
Big Mouth

75
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,480
and Teaty.

76
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,680
They live together.

77
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:04,360
Surely they'll take care of him.

78
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:08,400
But I want to do something for Doggo too.

79
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:16,840
Speed it up!

80
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,400
I'm doing business here!

81
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:19,660
Yes, one sec.

82
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:23,520
Don't think you're my only client!

83
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,560
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

84
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,480
You think you're my only client?

85
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,800
Hurry up and move your cart!

86
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,840
How dare he bully our Doggo!

87
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:33,280
Let go!

88
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,000
Don't make a scene here.

89
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:34,720
If you do,

90
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,000
you'll cause trouble to him.

91
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,320
Hurry up!

92
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,520
Move them quickly!

93
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:39,640
I can't do business like this!

94
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:40,600
Move them quick!

95
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:43,680
Or don't buy from me anymore!

96
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,240
Hurry up!

97
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,840
Are you not going back to school?

98
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,880
What about you?

99
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:08,440
Why are you doing this?

100
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:10,360
Are you punishing yourself?

101
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,680
Why aren't you coming to school?

102
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:15,080
It's almost graduation, Doggo.

103
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:20,040
I've been complaining about my old man all these years.

104
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:22,320
Blaming him for letting mom go.

105
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:25,120
Complaining that he's so stingy on me.

106
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,200
I only realized after coming here

107
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,840
that my old man worked really hard.

108
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,000
He's helped many people around here.

109
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:34,160
I've actually never really known him.

110
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,120
Have you thought about

111
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,840
what kind of person he wants you to be then?

112
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,000
I feel very sorry for how I treated him.

113
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,000
So I want to continue his business.

114
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,400
Thanks.

115
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,080
I'll do it.

116
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:14,880
Leave it to me. It'll get your clothes dirty.

117
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:15,600
It's fine.

118
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,680
You need to go to school later.

119
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:17,480
Don't worry.

120
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:27,640
I'll do it.

121
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,360
Fresh pork!

122
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,560
Have a look!

123
00:08:36,560 --> 00:08:37,280
Fresh pork here!

124
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,200
Fresh pork!

125
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,000
Have a look here! Fresh pork!

126
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:40,880
Fresh pork!

127
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:41,760
Come over here!

128
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:43,320
Fresh pork!

129
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,440
Fresh pork here!

130
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,440
Have a look!

131
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:51,000
Fresh pork!

132
00:08:51,679 --> 00:08:53,760
Have a look! Fresh pork!

133
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:02,000
You don't need to come help me tomorrow.

134
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:07,120
We're bros. What're you talking about.

135
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,600
This is my own business anyway.

136
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:11,800
Besides,

137
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:13,040
the other uncles at the market will help me as well.

138
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,320
- Doggo. - Doggo.

139
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,360
You haven't been eating properly these days, have you?

140
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,520
Come eat at our house then!

141
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:23,360
Don't worry, I eat very well every meal.

142
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,080
I'm fine,

143
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,000
don't worry about me.

144
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,440
Alright, go home now.

145
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:31,520
Look after yourself.

146
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,600
Remember to eat.

147
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,440
Let us know if you need anything.

148
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,640
Take some rest.

149
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:36,520
Dad.

150
00:10:40,460 --> 00:10:41,080
What's the matter?

151
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:43,360
Feeling down?

152
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:44,800
Nothing.

153
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:48,120
It's just that I have a really good friend,

154
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,880
and something happened in his family.

155
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,760
I'm worried about him.

156
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,600
That boy?

157
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:56,600
Yeah.

158
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,120
His father passed away.

159
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:02,360
He might look like a cheeky boy

160
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:04,000
good for nothing

161
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,040
in your eyes,

162
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,640
but he's really kind to me.

163
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:10,240
Help him where you can then.

164
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,800
Nothing's bigger than life and death.

165
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:26,640
Jiao Jiao,

166
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,280
Sometimes,

167
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:33,320
you're like a boy,

168
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:36,320
and other times you're like a girl.

169
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:42,200
Your mom and I think it's such a bargain.

170
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:45,680
We only have to raise one, but it feels like we have two!

171
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:50,600
But now that you're growing up,

172
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,520
you're more like a girl now.

173
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,120
I'm not sure about that.

174
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:58,800
What I mean is that

175
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:00,600
actually

176
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,000
we could have

177
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:04,720
another boy

178
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:06,080
in the house... right?

179
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:14,800
Let me have a listen!

180
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:16,600
Let me listen!

181
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,680
What're you doing?

182
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:18,640
Let me have a listen!

183
00:12:21,340 --> 00:12:21,960
Mom!

184
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,640
I can hear my little brother inside!

185
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:26,360
I mean Jun Jun!

186
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:28,800
Silly!

187
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,520
He's all by himself now.

188
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:32,600
We wanted to take him into our house.

189
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:33,960
You've always been like

190
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,880
brother and sister anyway.

191
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:37,360
Is that ok?

192
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,720
Oh you're so sweet, daddy!

193
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:51,200
It's just one more person at the dining table. We'll manage.

194
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:01,400
Mom, put two more eggs in it!

195
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,360
With more eggs,

196
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,840
it'd become egg fries meat,

197
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,000
not egg fries rice!

198
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:09,600
Put in more meat for Doggo then!

199
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:10,280
More meat here.

200
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:11,240
Enough, that's enough!

201
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,000
I'll put in more for him.

202
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,680
What if he doesn't have enough to eat?

203
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:17,280
I care for Jun Jun too,

204
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:19,000
but you can't mess with cooking!

205
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,560
Look how it's like now!

206
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:22,880
Now go and bring that bowl for me.

207
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:25,000
Thanks.

208
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:28,440
Yes yes. Have a seat inside.

209
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:29,840
Hi, Jiao Jiao.

210
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:30,560
Hello, aunty.

211
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,040
There's a fire here?

212
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:37,760
Doggo?

213
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:41,440
Anran?

214
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:44,600
Li Anran!

215
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:46,480
Why are you setting a fire here!

216
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:47,720
I'm making fried egg.

217
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:48,680
You're making fried egg?

218
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:49,880
You're setting a fire!

219
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:51,160
I'm really making fried egg!

220
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,000
All this smoke here,

221
00:13:53,680 --> 00:13:55,280
I thought Doggo was gonna commit suicide!

222
00:13:58,280 --> 00:13:59,520
This is your fried egg?

223
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:03,400
Dark as coal.

224
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:04,720
Putting up this grand stage,

225
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:06,880
I thought you're making an egg buffet or something.

226
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,080
Never mind, I'll teach you.

227
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,240
Turn off the fire first.

228
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,240
Watch carefully.

229
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:24,520
So you need oil for this.

230
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,920
A pampered kid like you

231
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:31,520
don't even know how to cook an egg for the person you like.

232
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:32,880
I don't like him!

233
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,040
You don't?

234
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:36,120
Why else would you be here making him breakfast this early?

235
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:38,000
Well, you know.

236
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,840
He did a lot for me before.

237
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,080
I want to be a good friend to him too.

238
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:56,000
Done!

239
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:58,400
Difficult?

240
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,320
You act so careless normally,

241
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,480
but you're actually so capable.

242
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:11,920
Isn't that normal?

243
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:14,200
You act so proud and cold normally,

244
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:16,520
but who would've thought you'd do this for others?

245
00:15:17,280 --> 00:15:19,000
I'm not proud and cold,

246
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,520
I'm just a bit quieter than you all.

247
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:24,040
Don't tell this to others, can you do that?

248
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,520
Don't tell others you're quiet?

249
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:28,360
No, don't tell others

250
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,000
I came to his house to do this.

251
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:30,600
Ok.

252
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,360
I wanted to make dinner as well.

253
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,200
Really?

254
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:37,240
You? Making dinner?

255
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:39,120
What if I managed!

256
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,360
Besides, you're here to help me.

257
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:42,000
Seems like I'm the only one helping you.

258
00:15:57,160 --> 00:15:59,000
Wow, so many in a pack! Such a deal!

259
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,240
This is so expensive. It has to be good.

260
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:04,360
This color is nice, it must be good then.

261
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:06,280
I've never even seen this. Let's pass this one.

262
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,560
You see the situation Doggo's in.

263
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:12,320
Why isn't anyone taking care of him?

264
00:16:12,320 --> 00:16:13,240
Where's his mom?

265
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:16,280
His mom left when he was eight

266
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,680
to another city.

267
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:19,400
She has her own children and family now.

268
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:21,400
He aged significantly

269
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:23,240
since then.

270
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:25,200
That's why we call him Doggo.

271
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:30,760
Let's make up for the motherly love he missed!

272
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:40,760
Am I qualified?

273
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:42,280
Yes.

274
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:45,360
Don't suck up to me

275
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,640
just because you want me to help you make dinner!

276
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:48,480
I can tell.

277
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,040
But if Doggo has motherly love,

278
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:51,560
he won't be so aged then.

279
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:52,840
Does that make him...a puppy then?

280
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,120
Puppy.

281
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:57,000
So adorable!

282
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,040
Let's raise a puppy together then!

283
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:00,520
I like this color too.

284
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,760
Big Mouth got good grades this time.

285
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:07,320
He works hard at night by himself!

286
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:08,260
Jiao Jiao!

287
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:11,400
You're besties now?

288
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:20,200
Jiao is so capable now.

289
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:53,120
What do you think you're doing?

290
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:54,800
I went to your school

291
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,360
and the teachers told me you haven't been back.

292
00:17:58,440 --> 00:17:59,960
I asked you to come to Chengdu with me

293
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:01,000
and you were unwilling.

294
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,360
What is it that you want?

295
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:04,520
I want to stay here.

296
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:05,200
Stay here for what?

297
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,000
Doing this good-for-nothing business?

298
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:09,520
Say something!

299
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:12,840
I'm working hard to carry on my old man business.

300
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:14,760
By the way, mom,

301
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:16,480
Do you know

302
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:17,920
how the people of this market

303
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:19,480
comment on my old man?

304
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:22,120
He's actually a very nice man.

305
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,680
Why did you leave him back then?

306
00:18:27,760 --> 00:18:29,600
Your dad wasn't good-tempered when he was young.

307
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:32,480
Of course, mom was young too.

308
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:33,920
We didn't know better and fought a lot.

309
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:36,840
Now that I think of it,

310
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:38,520
it was probably all trivial.

311
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,720
Jun Jun, let mom ask you something.

312
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:45,160
Do you feel that

313
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:48,240
you don't have any chance to pay back to your dad

314
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:50,720
and you feel sorry for it.

315
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:53,080
Are you trying to make up to him?

316
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:02,120
When your dad was still around,

317
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:03,120
whenever he called,

318
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:04,760
as soon as he picked up the phone

319
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:06,080
he wouldn't stop talking about you.

320
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:09,160
He talks about your running,

321
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,720
you liking which girl,

322
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:12,720
you being happy

323
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:14,040
or unhappy.

324
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:16,320
Anyway, I think

325
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:18,360
I think...

326
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:21,000
He wouldn't want to

327
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,080
see you like this.

328
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:25,840
All of you are telling me

329
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:28,400
that my old man wouldn't want to see me like this.

330
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:31,360
But I also don't want to see

331
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:33,360
the most important thing to my old man disappear.

332
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,680
Every time I see that this pork stall is still here,

333
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:40,360
I feel that my dad's still here.

334
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:43,480
Mom.

335
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:46,760
Let me make my own decision.

336
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:06,480
Smash it then chop it, like this.

337
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:14,000
Not too much.

338
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:15,760
Be careful.

339
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:19,400
I'll grab you some toothpaste.

340
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:21,680
It works well on scalds.

341
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:33,200
Yeah!

342
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:34,280
Let me try.

343
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:36,080
Save them for Doggo!

344
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:37,960
You only care for your Doggo, not me!

345
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:39,200
I taught you to make these!

346
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:39,920
I'll take you out to eat then.

347
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:40,720
Let's go.

348
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:41,800
I'll eat the most expensive thing then!

349
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:42,560
Ok ok.

350
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,840
So terrible!

351
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,000
REMEMBER TO EAT

352
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:54,880
Why are the dishes of Teaty's house

353
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:56,120
so different?

354
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:59,280
Jiao Jiao is such a capable cook now.

355
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:00,280
Why?

356
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:02,200
Such big breakfasts every day.

357
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:04,760
Fried rice, fried egg, bread, coffee.

358
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:06,640
Chinese and western, combined.

359
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:11,160
But we only made you a bowl of fried rice!

360
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:13,160
Jiao Jiao?

361
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:16,200
Since when do you know how to make coffee and bread?

362
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:18,040
It wasn't me, it was Anran.

363
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:19,880
What has it to do with Anran?

364
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,800
She's very close with me these days,

365
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:23,920
so I looked at what she eats

366
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:25,400
and tried to make them.

367
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,760
Can you make me some coffee

368
00:22:27,760 --> 00:22:28,920
and bread tomorrow then?

369
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:31,120
Don't just make it for him but not your old man.

370
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:33,080
That sounds so strange.

371
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,240
I'll see if I feel like it.

372
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:37,720
Uncle,

373
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:39,880
the fried egg is honestly so bad.

374
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:42,400
The fried egg is like a rock,

375
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:44,040
so rocky hard

376
00:22:44,120 --> 00:22:44,960
you can't even bite into it.

377
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:46,640
That sounds scary.

378
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:49,520
What're you laughing at?

379
00:22:50,760 --> 00:22:53,000
It sounds really bad.

380
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,440
You knew it was bad, didn't you?

381
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:55,920
You knew it was bad and you brought it to me.

382
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:56,960
What kind of friend are you?

383
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:57,720
Anran...

384
00:22:57,720 --> 00:22:59,840
Anran surely won't cook this badly.

385
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:04,320
Uncle, aunty, thanks for the food.

386
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:11,000
Sure, Anran cooks the best!

387
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,320
Jiao Jiao,

388
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:15,040
a girl will have a hard time finding a husband

389
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:16,600
if she doesn't cook well.

390
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:31,440
Am I too late?

391
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:36,160
I'm sorry.

392
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:49,480
Do you remember it?

393
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:51,920
Back when we were in primary school,

394
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,440
we tried to copy the ceremony to become brothers.

395
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:57,440
We went to your old man's shop,

396
00:23:57,440 --> 00:23:58,920
stole a pig's head out,

397
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:01,840
and stuck three incense sticks on it.

398
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:06,040
We were beaten into pulps by your old man.

399
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:08,840
Butcher was so scary!

400
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:12,560
Chasing after us.

401
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:19,960
How time flies.

402
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:22,720
Do you remember

403
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:24,200
what we said then?

404
00:24:26,040 --> 00:24:27,000
We said

405
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:29,120
"My old man is yours

406
00:24:29,520 --> 00:24:31,240
and yours mine.

407
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:33,680
My mom's yours

408
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,840
and yours mine.

409
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:40,080
If one day,

410
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:45,000
we fell in love with the same girl,

411
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:47,160
we're damned

412
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:48,560
and fall out of love together then."

413
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:00,080
We were so silly back then.

414
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:04,320
Yeah...

415
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:09,920
I only realized now...

416
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:13,080
Growing up is actually so complicated.

417
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:17,080
Very complicated indeed.

418
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:23,760
My brother,

419
00:25:30,480 --> 00:25:32,520
I really don't know how to comfort you.

420
00:25:35,560 --> 00:25:38,120
I don't even know how to comfort myself.

421
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:43,560
If it's this difficult with training already,

422
00:27:43,560 --> 00:27:45,000
what're we gonna do with the race?

423
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:48,960
Seems like Doggo is really not coming back.

424
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:53,320
No idea what he's thinking.

425
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:57,920
Can you persuade him somehow?

426
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:01,880
Doggo is a very stubborn one.

427
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:05,760
What's Doggo gonna do then?

428
00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:16,440
Cut it finer!

429
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:19,240
Can you do it or not?

430
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:22,400
Do you wanna show me?

431
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:23,360
What?

432
00:28:23,520 --> 00:28:24,920
I'm buying meat from you

433
00:28:24,920 --> 00:28:26,360
and I have to do the job myself?

434
00:28:26,360 --> 00:28:27,480
I don't mean it that way.

435
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:28,960
So all you do is hang your meat up?

436
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:31,560
I know it's not fine enough myself.

437
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:33,600
Enough, enough. Pack it for me.

438
00:28:45,080 --> 00:28:46,040
What's this?

439
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:48,160
You haven't been to school for so long

440
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:50,040
you forgot I'm your "one-on-one" study pal!

441
00:28:50,040 --> 00:28:51,240
No need for that anymore.

442
00:28:51,240 --> 00:28:52,360
Why?

443
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,320
I'm not going back to school.

444
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:55,680
Don't be childish.

445
00:28:57,280 --> 00:28:58,240
I'm being serious.

446
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:03,000
I saw an American film recently.

447
00:29:03,320 --> 00:29:04,480
Watch this

448
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:05,520
if you don't want to read.

449
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:08,400
What film?

450
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:09,600
Forrest Gump.

451
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:12,080
What's it about?

452
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:15,080
It's about a man who seems to be a fool

453
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:16,360
but not quite.

454
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:17,320
He's a lot like you.

455
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:20,000
And then?

456
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:23,280
He's gained a lot

457
00:29:23,320 --> 00:29:24,960
but none of them seem to be what he wants.

458
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:28,280
The things he really wanted, he didn't seem to grasp any.

459
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:30,360
All his loved ones

460
00:29:30,360 --> 00:29:31,520
left him.

461
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:34,920
Sounds miserable.

462
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:37,840
What's he gonna do then?

463
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:40,400
And then one day,

464
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:41,840
he started running.

465
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:44,360
He kept running forward.

466
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:47,000
He kept running?

467
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:48,480
Kept running.

468
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,280
Why's he running?

469
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:53,000
No idea.

470
00:30:01,920 --> 00:30:03,080
Well. he is a fool then.

471
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:09,600
How've you been recently?

472
00:30:11,360 --> 00:30:12,440
I've been well.

473
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,480
Having enough to eat, enough to wear?

474
00:30:15,560 --> 00:30:17,560
Their family are so kind to me.

475
00:30:17,560 --> 00:30:19,160
So kind I feel a little embarrassed.

476
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:21,200
Don't be.

477
00:30:21,240 --> 00:30:23,600
Don't starve yourself because you're embarrassed,

478
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:24,440
you understand?

479
00:30:25,040 --> 00:30:27,960
The only thing is the level of cooking is really... random.

480
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:29,160
Some of the dishes are so bad.

481
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:30,720
Like which?

482
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:32,240
There was this fried cucumber with meat.

483
00:30:32,240 --> 00:30:33,280
The cucumbers were black!

484
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:34,240
They fried it with their feet?

485
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:35,840
What else?

486
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:37,400
And the tomato and egg.

487
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:38,600
Normally in this dish,

488
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:40,040
you'd put sugar or salt.

489
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:41,040
But the one I got,

490
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:42,040
you have no idea what's inside.

491
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:43,160
Vinegar!

492
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:44,800
I suspect that the person

493
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:46,880
wasn't thinking about cooking at all when making...

494
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:49,280
You deserve to be starved to death!

495
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:50,840
Others worked so hard to cook for you,

496
00:30:50,840 --> 00:30:52,040
how can you say that?

497
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:53,240
What're you mad for? You didn't make them!

498
00:30:53,240 --> 00:30:53,860
It's just me!

499
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:57,960
It's just that I think

500
00:30:58,400 --> 00:30:59,640
if others worked so hard to cook for you,

501
00:30:59,640 --> 00:31:01,480
you shouldn't say it's bad like this.

502
00:31:02,040 --> 00:31:03,040
But it really is very bad.

503
00:31:03,040 --> 00:31:03,960
It's like food for dog.

504
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:05,200
It is food for dog!

505
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:06,280
You're called Doggo anyway!

506
00:31:06,280 --> 00:31:07,680
What right have you to say the food is bad?

507
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:09,960
Why are you so angry? What's the problem?

508
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:12,600
It's one thing if the dishes are good,

509
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:14,360
it's another thing if you deserve them!

510
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:18,080
Hey, you're going already?

511
00:31:18,080 --> 00:31:19,280
Not buying me dinner or something?

512
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:20,240
You don't deserve it!

513
00:31:30,760 --> 00:31:32,200
So special.

514
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:34,320
Cares for me in one moment,

515
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:35,600
mad at me in another.

516
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:53,640
What! I'm working on my lyrics!

517
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:05,320
Super Girl.

518
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:08,080
Contestant, Zhu Weijiao.

519
00:32:08,600 --> 00:32:09,400
Good luck!

520
00:32:11,080 --> 00:32:13,560
Don't you know the most important thing now is the exam?

521
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,360
Why're you wasting your time on these?

522
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:17,440
Didn't you have enough at the new year's event?

523
00:32:18,400 --> 00:32:20,840
Come on, go up and sing for the class.

524
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:25,440
Round of applause for her, everyone!

525
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:30,680
Come on.

526
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:41,840
Sir,

527
00:32:41,840 --> 00:32:43,200
I think what you're doing is not right.

528
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:44,520
What did you say, Ma Tian?

529
00:32:45,080 --> 00:32:47,000
I said, sir, I think what you're doing is not right.

530
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:47,920
I'm not right?

531
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:49,680
What you are doing will make students think

532
00:32:49,680 --> 00:32:51,520
that having a dream and pursuing it

533
00:32:51,600 --> 00:32:53,640
is something to be embarrassed and ashamed of.

534
00:32:53,840 --> 00:32:56,320
I just don't want anyone to waste time

535
00:32:56,320 --> 00:32:57,640
like this right now.

536
00:32:58,000 --> 00:32:59,920
But I don't think this is wasting time.

537
00:32:59,920 --> 00:33:02,000
Compared to this, being afraid of what others think

538
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:04,160
and not speaking out and realizing their dreams

539
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:05,320
for their whole life, that's really wasting time.

540
00:33:06,120 --> 00:33:07,640
Sir, I think Ma Tian is right.

541
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:12,320
I've always thought the two of you

542
00:33:12,320 --> 00:33:13,680
are good students.

543
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:15,160
Sir,

544
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:16,840
I also think Ma Tian is right!

545
00:33:18,420 --> 00:33:19,040
Why,

546
00:33:19,680 --> 00:33:20,720
you have a dream too?

547
00:33:21,280 --> 00:33:22,880
Not... yet.

548
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:44,560
That's not true!

549
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:45,600
I have a dream!

550
00:33:46,280 --> 00:33:47,040
Sir!

551
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:48,720
My dream is

552
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:51,960
Chen Yuanyuan!

553
00:33:56,960 --> 00:33:57,800
Finally.

554
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:13,120
I signed up for you the other day.

555
00:34:20,840 --> 00:34:22,159
Sign up for what?

556
00:34:25,080 --> 00:34:26,360
Super Girls.

557
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:27,480
Chengdu Audition.

558
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:30,520
I haven't actually thought it through yet...

559
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:34,320
I'll be there with you then.

560
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:35,480
There's nothing to be afraid of.

561
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:56,199
Ding Rongliang!

562
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:00,360
What did you do this time?

563
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:01,280
Wh... Wha... What is it?

564
00:35:03,080 --> 00:35:03,840
Stop!

565
00:35:08,640 --> 00:35:09,760
Your pant scarf.

566
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,200
For you.

567
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:14,280
I made it better.

568
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:16,160
And I'm keeping the other for myself.

569
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:22,800
Teaty my bro!

570
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:25,960
My guide is finally working!

571
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:12,800
This doesn't look like the style of Hercules Jiao...

572
00:37:16,240 --> 00:37:18,600
Even two fish for me!

573
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:26,520
This painting...

574
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:28,400
looks so cheap.

575
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:32,560
They're surely getting tackier by the day.

576
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:42,680
They really think I'm a dog or what?

577
00:38:03,120 --> 00:38:03,720
Never mind.

578
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:07,320
Your little brat's not gonna tell you stories today.

579
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:08,480
Today, I'm

580
00:38:08,600 --> 00:38:10,160
gonna sing you a song!

581
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:12,960
The name of the song is

582
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:16,600
"The Moon Speaks For Me".

583
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:24,360
You asked me how deeply I love you,

584
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:28,400
to what extent is my love.

585
00:39:56,960 --> 00:39:57,580
Thanks.

586
00:39:58,720 --> 00:39:59,600
Anran!

587
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:04,000
You...

588
00:40:04,080 --> 00:40:05,360
I... I...

589
00:40:06,200 --> 00:40:06,800
I know!

590
00:40:06,920 --> 00:40:08,800
You're here for your good friend Hercules Jiao, am I right?

591
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:10,960
Her house...

592
00:40:11,560 --> 00:40:13,080
Her house is that way, not here.

593
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:13,760
I... I...

594
00:40:15,600 --> 00:40:16,440
Since we're classmates,

595
00:40:16,580 --> 00:40:17,200
I'll take you there.

596
00:40:17,280 --> 00:40:17,880
No, I'm fine, really...

597
00:40:17,880 --> 00:40:18,880
You don't know your directions around here.

598
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:19,480
Let's go!

599
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:20,400
Come on!

600
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:25,600
Jiao Jiao!

601
00:40:26,080 --> 00:40:26,720
Jiao Jiao!

602
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:27,920
I brought your good friend

603
00:40:28,080 --> 00:40:29,160
over to see you!

604
00:40:29,340 --> 00:40:29,960
Jiao Jiao!

605
00:40:30,200 --> 00:40:30,800
Jiao Jiao!

606
00:40:32,640 --> 00:40:34,640
She was searching her way around at Doggo's place,

607
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:35,840
looking so lost.

608
00:40:36,360 --> 00:40:37,360
You have to thank me!

609
00:40:38,160 --> 00:40:39,400
Alright, alright, I see.

610
00:40:40,120 --> 00:40:41,280
- See ya. - Jiao Jiao!

611
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:07,280
Be more careful next time you go to Doggo's place!

612
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:08,040
I will.

613
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:10,600
I really don't understand girls like you.

614
00:41:11,040 --> 00:41:12,520
If I did this much,

615
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:13,840
I'd want the whole damn world

616
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:14,800
to know that I did it.

617
00:41:14,800 --> 00:41:15,520
But you're

618
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:16,880
hiding around

619
00:41:16,880 --> 00:41:18,160
in the corner and all that.

620
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:19,560
But if he found out

621
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:21,000
he'll surely be embarrassed.

622
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:22,120
I just think that

623
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:23,720
he needs someone to take care of him these days.

624
00:41:24,560 --> 00:41:25,560
And he's not buying it.

625
00:41:25,560 --> 00:41:27,640
He said your cooking was awful.

626
00:41:27,640 --> 00:41:29,120
He said that to you too?

627
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:31,240
And he blames me for it!

628
00:41:32,440 --> 00:41:34,200
Thank God he doesn't know it's me...

629
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:36,080
You really care this much about what he thinks of you?

630
00:41:37,040 --> 00:41:38,680
You do like Doggo, don't you,

631
00:41:38,680 --> 00:41:39,720
even just a little?

632
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:41,960
Of course I like him!

633
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:43,480
We're deskmates, after all.

634
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:45,000
Of course she likes you!

635
00:41:45,560 --> 00:41:46,880
Just because you're deskmates?

636
00:42:54,120 --> 00:42:54,880
You made...

637
00:42:58,520 --> 00:42:59,480
those dishes?

638
00:43:33,600 --> 00:43:35,600
I learned this from you.

639
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:39,240
Not everything you do for others needs to be seen.

640
00:43:42,720 --> 00:43:43,600
If I knew...

641
00:43:44,320 --> 00:43:45,480
those dishes were from you...

642
00:43:49,160 --> 00:43:50,560
I would never have said those things.

643
00:43:52,120 --> 00:43:53,840
I know they're bad myself.

644
00:43:57,320 --> 00:43:57,960
They're... good.

645
00:43:59,080 --> 00:43:59,760
So fake.
